--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BinAbsInspector — Tencent Keenlab
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Design inspiration. BinAbsInspector is a static analysis tool for automated
binary vulnerability detection built on Ghidra's Pcode IR and abstract
interpretation. autopsy borrows its conceptual model — whole-program flow
analysis for CWE-aligned vulnerability detection — while taking an entirely
different, angr-backed, Python-native implementation path.

    https://github.com/KeenSecurityLab/BinAbsInspector

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
angr — SecureSystemsLab (and the angr project contributors)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Underlying analysis engine. autopsy uses angr (and its bundled components cle,
pyvex, and claripy) for binary loading, control-flow recovery, and symbolic
reachability analysis. angr is released under the BSD 2-Clause License.

    https://github.com/angr/angr
    https://angr.io
